label: Historisk Tidskrift för Finland
title: Historisk_Tidskrift_för_Finland
exrest: Historisk Tidskrift för Finland is a Swedish-language Finnish history journal which has been published by the Historiska föreningen since 1916. It was founded in 1916 by Per Olof von Törne, who had founded the Svenska studenters historiska förening two years earlier. He served as the journal's editor until 1924. With support for translation from the Delegation for the Promotion of Swedish Literature, managed by the Society of Swedish Literature in Finland, the journal is now also a forum for Finnish-speaking historians. The journal is published four times a year and has approximately 550 subscribers, primarily from Finland, the Nordic countries, and the Baltic region. Each paper is reviewed by two external referees.
